<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<Defs>

  <GeneDef ParentName="GeneEyeColor">
    <defName>DRG_Eyes_Gold</defName>
    <label>gold eyes</label>
    <labelShortAdj>gold-eyed</labelShortAdj>
    <description>Carriers of this gene have striking amber gold eyes.</description>
    <iconPath>UI/Icons/Genes/Gene_GoldEyes</iconPath>
    <displayOrderInCategory>2</displayOrderInCategory>
    <renderNodeProperties>
      <li Class="PawnRenderNodeProperties_Eye">
        <texPath>Things/Pawn/Humanlike/HeadAttachments/GoldEyes/GoldEyes_Male</texPath>
        <texPathFemale>Things/Pawn/Humanlike/HeadAttachments/GoldEyes/GoldEyes_Female</texPathFemale>
        <rotDrawMode>Fresh, Rotting</rotDrawMode>
        <parentTagDef>Head</parentTagDef>
        <drawSize>1.0</drawSize>
        <drawData>
          <defaultData>
            <layer>54</layer>
            <offset>(0, 0, 0)</offset>
          </defaultData>
        </drawData>
      </li>
    </renderNodeProperties>
  </GeneDef>

  <GeneDef ParentName="GeneSkinColorOverride">
    <defName>DRG_Skin_PaperWhite</defName>
    <label>paper white skin</label>
    <labelShortAdj>pallid</labelShortAdj>
    <description>Carriers of this gene have extremely pale and near translucent skin, a cosmetic side effect of an accelerated growth matrix.</description>
    <skinColorOverride>(224, 213, 205)</skinColorOverride>
    <displayOrderInCategory>69</displayOrderInCategory>
    <symbolPack>
      <prefixSymbols>
        <li>
          <symbol>pale</symbol>
        </li>
        <li>
          <symbol>pallid</symbol>
        </li>
      </prefixSymbols>
    </symbolPack>
  </GeneDef>

  <GeneDef>
    <defName>DRG_Replicant_AcceleratedAging</defName>
    <label>rapid senescence</label>
    <labelShortAdj>fast-aging</labelShortAdj>
    <description>Carriers of this gene age at a normal rate through early life. Past thirty the body begins to outpace itself, burning through remaining biological years at an accelerating rate.</description>
    <iconPath>UI/Icons/Genes/Gene_RapidSenescence</iconPath>
    <displayCategory>Miscellaneous</displayCategory>
    <displayOrderInCategory>100</displayOrderInCategory>
    <biologicalAgeTickFactorFromAgeCurve>
      <points>
        <li>(0, 2)</li>
        <li>(20, 3)</li>
        <li>(40, 4)</li>
      </points>
    </biologicalAgeTickFactorFromAgeCurve>
    <biostatCpx>2</biostatCpx>
    <biostatMet>4</biostatMet>
    <customEffectDescriptions>
      <li>Twice the aging from birth to 20.</li>
      <li>Thrice the aging rate to 40.</li>
      <li>Four times the aging rate after 40.</li>
    </customEffectDescriptions>
    <symbolPack>
      <wholeNameSymbols>
        <li><symbol>fast-lifer</symbol></li>
        <li><symbol>brief-lifer</symbol></li>
      </wholeNameSymbols>
    </symbolPack>
  </GeneDef>

  <GeneDef ParentName="GeneLearningBase">
    <defName>DRG_Replicant_Conditioning</defName>
    <label>accelerated conditioning</label>
    <labelShortAdj>conditioned</labelShortAdj>
    <description>Carriers of this gene have neural pathways optimized from birth through an intensive conditioning program. They absorb and retain skills at a considerably faster rate than others. It does not make them smarter. It makes them efficient.</description>
    <iconPath>UI/Icons/Genes/Gene_Conditioning</iconPath>
    <displayCategory>Miscellaneous</displayCategory>
    <displayOrderInCategory>101</displayOrderInCategory>
    <statOffsets>
      <GlobalLearningFactor>1.5</GlobalLearningFactor>
    </statOffsets>
    <biostatCpx>3</biostatCpx>
    <biostatMet>-5</biostatMet>
    <symbolPack>
      <prefixSymbols>
        <li><symbol>conditioned</symbol></li>
        <li><symbol>primed</symbol></li>
        <li><symbol>trained</symbol></li>
      </prefixSymbols>
    </symbolPack>
  </GeneDef>

  <GeneDef>
    <defName>DRG_Replicant_FinalClarity</defName>
    <label>final clarity</label>
    <labelShortAdj>clarity-bound</labelShortAdj>
    <description>At the end of their biological life, carriers of this gene experience a profound mental opening. For however long remains to them they become extraordinary at everything they do. The phenomenon has no accepted scientific explanation.</description>
    <iconPath>UI/Icons/Genes/Gene_FinalClarity</iconPath>
    <displayCategory>Miscellaneous</displayCategory>
    <displayOrderInCategory>102</displayOrderInCategory>
    <geneClass>ReplicantXenotype.Gene_FinalClarity</geneClass>
    <biostatCpx>2</biostatCpx>
    <biostatMet>-2</biostatMet>
    <customEffectDescriptions>
      <li>At biological age 40, triggers a permanent state of extraordinary capability.</li>
      <li>Work speed, melee damage, move speed, and social ability are greatly increased.</li>
      <li>Pain is suppressed and consciousness is elevated.</li>
      <li>This triggers only once.</li>
    </customEffectDescriptions>
    <symbolPack>
      <wholeNameSymbols>
        <li><symbol>clarity</symbol></li>
        <li><symbol>lastlight</symbol></li>
      </wholeNameSymbols>
    </symbolPack>
  </GeneDef>

  <GeneDef>
    <defName>DRG_Replicant_TemperatureResilience</defName>
    <label>temperature resilience</label>
    <labelShortAdj>resilient</labelShortAdj>
    <description>Carriers of this gene have modified thermoregulatory systems that allow them to function in environments that would incapacitate unmodified humans. They are comfortable in both extreme heat and extreme cold.</description>
    <displayCategory>Temperature</displayCategory>
    <displayOrderInCategory>103</displayOrderInCategory>
    <iconPath>UI/Icons/Genes/Gene_TemperatureResilience</iconPath>
    <statOffsets>
      <ComfyTemperatureMin>-10</ComfyTemperatureMin>
      <ComfyTemperatureMax>10</ComfyTemperatureMax>
    </statOffsets>
    <biostatCpx>2</biostatCpx>
    <biostatMet>-2</biostatMet>
    <customEffectDescriptions>
      <li>Comfortable temperature minimum reduced by 10 degrees.</li>
      <li>Comfortable temperature maximum increased by 10 degrees.</li>
    </customEffectDescriptions>
    <symbolPack>
      <prefixSymbols>
        <li><symbol>hardy</symbol></li>
        <li><symbol>dura</symbol></li>
        <li><symbol>temper</symbol></li>
      </prefixSymbols>
    </symbolPack>
  </GeneDef>

  <GeneDef ParentName="FertilityBase">
    <defName>DRG_Replicant_LowFertility</defName>
    <label>low fertility</label>
    <labelShortAdj>infertile</labelShortAdj>
    <description>Carriers of this gene have a greatly reduced capacity for natural reproduction. Conception is possible but deeply unlikely without intervention.</description>
    <iconPath>UI/Icons/Genes/Gene_LowFertility</iconPath>
    <displayCategory>Reproduction</displayCategory>
    <displayOrderInCategory>105</displayOrderInCategory>
    <statFactors>
      <Fertility>0.2</Fertility>
    </statFactors>
    <biostatMet>2</biostatMet>
    <symbolPack>
      <prefixSymbols>
        <li><symbol>barren</symbol></li>
        <li><symbol>sparse</symbol></li>
      </prefixSymbols>
    </symbolPack>
  </GeneDef>

<GeneDef ParentName="CellInstabilityBase">
    <defName>DRG_Replicant_CellInstability</defName>
    <label>accelerated cell instability</label>
    <labelShortAdj>unstable</labelShortAdj>
    <description>Carriers of this gene have deeply unstable cell replication machinery, a consequence of the rapid growth matrix embedded in their genetics from inception. The body runs fast and it runs poorly. Eventually it runs out.</description>
    <iconPath>UI/Icons/Genes/Gene_MajorCellInstability</iconPath>
    <displayOrderInCategory>104</displayOrderInCategory>
    <biostatMet>4</biostatMet>
    <statFactors>
      <LifespanFactor>0.6</LifespanFactor>
      <CancerRate>8</CancerRate>
      <ImmunityGainSpeed>0.92</ImmunityGainSpeed>
    </statFactors>
  </GeneDef>  

</Defs>